<p><strong>Explanation</strong></p>
<p>Long story short, the relevant, buggy piece of code within <em>bowser!Dr=
iverEntry</em> is represented by the following pseudo-code:</p>
<div><div id=3D"highlighter_798942" class=3D"syntaxhighlighter  c"><table b=
order=3D"0" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0"><tbody><tr><td class=3D"gut=
ter"><div class=3D"line number1 index0 alt2">1</div><div class=3D"line numb=
er2 index1 alt1">2</div><div class=3D"line number3 index2 alt2">3</div><div=
 class=3D"line number4 index3 alt1">4</div><div class=3D"line number5 index=
4 alt2">5</div><div class=3D"line number6 index5 alt1">6</div></td><td clas=
s=3D"code"><div class=3D"container"><div class=3D"line number1 index0 alt2"=
><code class=3D"c spaces">&nbsp;&nbsp;</code><code class=3D"c plain">RtlIni=
tUnicodeString(&amp;BowserNameString, </code><code class=3D"c string">L"\\D=
evice\\LanmanDatagramReceiver"</code><code class=3D"c plain">);</code></div=
><div class=3D"line number2 index1 alt1"><code class=3D"c spaces">&nbsp;&nb=
sp;</code><code class=3D"c plain">IoCreateDevice(DriverObject, 0, &amp;Bows=
erNameString, 0x13u, 0, 0, &amp;DeviceObject);</code></div><div class=3D"li=
ne number3 index2 alt2">&nbsp;</div><div class=3D"line number4 index3 alt1"=
><code class=3D"c plain">[...]</code></div><div class=3D"line number5 index=
4 alt2">&nbsp;</div><div class=3D"line number6 index5 alt1"><code class=3D"=
c spaces">&nbsp;&nbsp;</code><code class=3D"c plain">ObGetObjectSecurity(De=
viceObject, &amp;SecurityDescriptor, MemoryAllocated);</code></div></div></=
td></tr></tbody></table></div></div>
<p style=3D"text-align: justify;">The driver tries to create a device with =
a fixed name and after returning from the <em>IoCreateDevice</em> call, it =
blindly assumes that the operation has succeeded; if it is the second insta=
nce of the module in the operating system, the assumption is broken, result=
ing in numerous dereferences of the NULL address treated as a device object=
 pointer.</p>
