<p><strong>Explanation</strong></p>
<p style=3D"text-align: justify;">Similarly to Diskdump.sys, the Dumpata.sy=
s driver appears to interpret the second parameter of <em>DriverEntry</em> =
differently from its typical meaning. This time, an internal <em>IdeDumpPor=
tInitializ</em><em>e</em> function treats some of unicode string=E2=80=99s =
bytes as a virtual memory address and tries to access it=E2=80=A6 with no c=
hance to succeed.</p>
