<p><strong>Explanation</strong></p>
<p style=3D"text-align: justify;">The dxg.sys executable imports several fu=
nctions from the primary Windows graphical driver =E2=80=93 win32k.sys. As =
the latter image resides in so called <em>session memory</em> which is only=
 mapped in threads marked as GUI and the process of resolving dxg.sys depen=
dencies takes place in a non-GUI <em>System</em> process, a fatal exception=
 is raised upon trying to access the&nbsp;base address of the win32k.sys im=
age.</p>
