<p><strong>Explanation</strong></p>
<p>Although a NULL Pointer Dereference, this case is particularly funny. Th=
e affected part of <em>DriverEntry</em> works in the following way:</p>
<div><div id=3D"highlighter_394473" class=3D"syntaxhighlighter  c"><table b=
order=3D"0" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0"><tbody><tr><td class=3D"gut=
ter"><div class=3D"line number1 index0 alt2">1</div><div class=3D"line numb=
er2 index1 alt1">2</div><div class=3D"line number3 index2 alt2">3</div><div=
 class=3D"line number4 index3 alt1">4</div><div class=3D"line number5 index=
4 alt2">5</div></td><td class=3D"code"><div class=3D"container"><div class=
=3D"line number1 index0 alt2"><code class=3D"c keyword bold">if</code> <cod=
e class=3D"c plain">(failed(WdmlibIoCreateDeviceSecure(...))) {</code></div=
><div class=3D"line number2 index1 alt1"><code class=3D"c spaces">&nbsp;&nb=
sp;</code><code class=3D"c plain">DxgkSqmShutdown();</code></div><div class=
=3D"line number3 index2 alt2"><code class=3D"c plain">}</code></div><div cl=
ass=3D"line number4 index3 alt1"><code class=3D"c plain">[...]</code></div>=
<div class=3D"line number5 index4 alt2"><code class=3D"c plain">DxgkSqmInit=
();</code></div></div></td></tr></tbody></table></div></div>
<p style=3D"text-align: justify;">Both routines operate on a shared structu=
re pointed to by a global dxgkrnl!<em>pDxgkSqmControl</em> pointer. The poi=
nter is initialized for the first time in the <em>DxgkSqmInit</em> function=
, therefore it is still equal to NULL at the time of calling <em>DxgkSqmShu=
tdown</em>.&nbsp;The deinitialization proc doesn=E2=80=99t expect <em>pDxgk=
SqmControl</em> to be zero and simply starts destroying and cleaning up par=
ticular fields within the structure, which results in an unhandled exceptio=
n at the first attempt of using the pointer in a memory operation.</p>
